Formulae which express trigonometric functions of $(A+B)$ in terms of trigonometric functions of $A$ and $B$.

$$\cos(A+B)=\cos(A)\cos(B) - \sin(A)\sin(B)$$
$$\sin(A+B)=\cos(A)\sin(B) + \sin(A)\cos(B)$$
$$\tan(A+B)=\frac{\tan(A)+\tan(B)}{1-\tan(A)\tan(B)}$$

For trigonometric functions of e.g. $(A-B)$, replace $B$ in these formulae with $-B$ and use the appropriate properties of $\sin$, $\cos$ and $\tan$.
